To count the occurrences of a specific word in a text file, you can use a C++ program with the `std::string` and `std::ifstream` libraries. Here's a simple example:
```cpp
#include <string>
#include <fstream>

int main() {
    std::ifstream file(“input.txt”);
    std::string line;

    while (file.good()) {
        std::getline(file, line);
        if (line.empty()) {
            continue;
        }

        int count = 0;
        for (const auto& word : line.strings()) {
            if (word.compare(“your_specific_word”) == 0) {
                count++;
            }
        }

        std::cout << “Word “ << count << “ appears “ << count << “ times” << std::endl;
    }

    return 0;
}
```
This program reads the input text file line by line and counts the occurrences of the specific word. You can replace the word “your_specific_word” with the word you want to count. The output will show how many times the specified word appears in the input file.

